<recipe 
xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd"> 
                                                                                
    <title>Okonomiyaki</title>
    <filename>okonomiyaki.xml</filename>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>

    <part>
        <title>Main</title>
        <ingredient>1 cup flour</ingredient>
        <ingredient>2 eggs</ingredient>
        <ingredient>160 gms chicken stock </ingredient>
        <ingredient>2 spring onions chopped</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/8 cabbage shredded </ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 zucchini grated</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 small carrot grated</ingredient>
        <ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Oil for frying</ingredient>
        <step>Whisk eggs in a large bowl, add flour, stock and salt and pepper and whisk to combine. Stir in all other ingredients. Heat oil in large pan and place about 1/2 cup of mixture making it as round as possible. You can place an amount of bacon and/or shrimp on pancake before flipping. Once edges start to cook flip over and cook other side. Flip over a couple of time to ensure middle cooked and both sides are golden. Remove from pan and garnish with sauces and spring onions and/or bacon if desired. Serve hot.</step>
    </part>

    <part>
        <title>Optional</title>
        <ingredient>Bacon</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Pickled ginger</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Shrimp</ingredient>
    </part>

    <part>
        <title>Toppings</title>
        <ingredient>Spring onions chopped</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Kewpie mayonnaise</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Okonomi sauce (or teriyaki sauce)</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Fried shallots</ingredient>
    </part>
</recipe>